Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000 (Races where entered for $12,500 or less not considered in eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FIRE ALARM pursued the loose pacesetter three wide, vied through the final turn and eagerly pulled away under constant handling. MAGIC HARBOR rallied to earn a narrow lead at the three eighths pole, dueled but proved no match for the winner. HOTCHA DO IT steered inside on the first turn, angled out on the final turn and offered a mild bid. GOLDEN RINGS quickly sprinted to a wide advantage, was caught after half a mile and faded. HOPPY DO steadied just after the start, was asked for run wide on the final turn with little response. SACRED GROUND lagged far behind and was always outrun. CITIZEN KAT lacked speed and never reached contention.

RECEPTION POINT lost contact with his field early and never a factor. DADDY'S THIEF injured himself in the starting gate and was ordered scratched by the stewards on the advice of the track veternarian. There was a seven minute delay in the post time for this race.
